ixing bowl and chop <b>10 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add eggs, fish sauce, lime, salt (optional), chilli flakes and oil and combine <b>20 sec\/speed 4<b>. Divide mixture between muffin holes and, using a spoon, stir to combine mixture in each muffin hole."},{"content":"Place muffin tray into a large casserole dish and fill dish halfway up the side of muffin tray with water. Bake for 30-35 minutes (180°C) or until cooked through. Serve warm or cold with sweet chilli sauce."}],"hintsAndTricks":["You can use a standard 12-hole muffin tray in this recipe.","Please refer to <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i> or the <i>Everyday Cookbook<\/i> for the Chicken stock paste recipe."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","40m","6 portions"]}